docs.lead_paragraph: Dr. RICE, the Health Commissioner of New York, attributes to immunizations the reduction in diphtheria deaths to "new record low marks" in the last two years. In 1936 there were only thirty-six such deaths, as compared with the annual average death toll from this dread disease for the tenyear period ending in 1929, which was about 750.
